rero\">Andrea Ferrero</a> - Developer of PhotoFlow image editor, maintains various Appimage packages.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T15:04:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"uraimo/awesome-software-patreons","categoryHTML":"<h2>People Doing Open Source Work</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/rurban\">Reini Urban</a> - Maintaining and developing software such as cperl, parrot, a lot of perl5 modules, safeclib and libredwg.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T15:04:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>General Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/project-jedi/jcl\">JCL</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/project-jedi/jcl\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">492</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":492,\"repo\":\"project-jedi/jcl\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Set of thoroughly tested and fully documented utility functions and non-visual classes which can be instantly reused in your Delphi and C++ Builder projects. The library is grouped into several categories such as Strings, Files and I/O, Security, Math and many, many more.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>General Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/project-jedi/jvcl\">JVCL</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/project-jedi/jvcl\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">463</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":463,\"repo\":\"project-jedi/jvcl\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> Library of over 600 Delphi components developed by \"Project JEDI\" members.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Audio</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://mac.sourceforge.net/atl\">Audio Tools Library</a>. <code>[Delphi]</code> For manipulating many audio formats file information.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Video</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://code.google.com/p/dspack\">DSPack</a> (abandoned, active fork is <a href=\"https://github.com/micha137/dspack-continued-mirror-for-delphinus\">here</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/micha137/dspack-continued-mirror-for-delphinus\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">16</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":16,\"repo\":\"micha137/dspack-continued-mirror-for-delphinus\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->). <code>[Delphi]</code> Set of components and classes to write Multimedia Applications using MS Direct Show and DirectX technologies.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Video</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Laex/Delphi-OpenCV\">Delphi-OpenCV</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Laex/Delphi-OpenCV\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">360</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":360,\"repo\":\"Laex/Delphi-OpenCV\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> Translation of OpenCV library header files in Delphi</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mike-lischke/GraphicEx\">GraphicEx</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mike-lischke/GraphicEx\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">80</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":80,\"repo\":\"mike-lischke/GraphicEx\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> Addendum to Delphi's Graphics.pas to enable your application to load many common image formats. This library is primarily designed to load images as background (buttons, forms, toolbars) and textures (DirectX, OpenGL) or for image browsing and editing purposes as long as you don't need to save images.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://code.google.com/p/ccr-exif\">CCR-EXIF</a> (seems abandoned, list of forks on GH <a href=\"https://github.com/search?l=Pascal&#x26;o=desc&#x26;q=ccr-exif&#x26;s=updated&#x26;type=Repositories\">here</a>). <code>[Delphi]</code> Library to read and write Exif, IPTC and XMP metadata from JPEG, TIFF and PSD images.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.tkweb.eu/en/delphicomp/kicon.html\">KIcon</a>. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> This component makes sense if a more complex manipulation with icons (or better icon files *.ico) than just viewing is needed. Full PNG icon image support, correct rendering, icons with alpha channel.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/synopse/SynPDF\">Synopse PDF</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/synopse/SynPDF\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">173</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":173,\"repo\":\"synopse/SynPDF\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Fully featured Open Source PDF document creation library for Delphi, embedded in one unit. Pure Delphi code, Delphi 5 up to Delphi 10.3 Rio (and latest version of FPC), for Win32 and Win64 platforms.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/igdiplus\">IGDI+</a>. <code>[Delphi]</code> The free open source library allows quick and easy implementations of complex GDI+ applications, in a natural Delphi-friendly code.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/glscene\">GLScene</a>. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> OpenGL based 3D library for Delphi, C++Builder and Lazarus. It provides visual components and objects allowing description and rendering of 3D scenes in an easy, no-hassle, yet powerful manner. GLScene is not just an OpenGL wrapper or utility library, it has grown to become a set of founding classes for a generic 3D engine with Rapid Application Development in mind. GLScene allows you to quickly design and render 3D scenes without having to learn the intricacies of OpenGL, if you know how to design a TForm, you'll easily master the basic operations of GLScene. The library comes with a large collections of demos showcasing the ease of use, and demonstrating RAD wasn't done at the expense of CPU/GPU horsepower.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/synopse/mORMot/blob/master/SynGdiPlus.pas\">SynGdiPlus</a>. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Enables an application to load and save GIF, TIF, PNG and JPG pictures. It also allows anti-aliased drawing from any TMetaFile. That is, you can play a .emf content using GDI+ instead of GDI, for much better rendering result.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/andorra\">Andorra 2D</a>. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> New generation 2D Engine for Delphi and Lazarus. Andorra 2D is capable to use DirectX or OpenGL through graphic plugins. Andorra 2D is built in a very modular way and is yet easy to use.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vintagedave/transparent-canvas\">Transparent-canvas</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vintagedave/transparent-canvas\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">39</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":39,\"repo\":\"vintagedave/transparent-canvas\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> Delphi VCL / Windows project for drawing semi-transparent alphablended graphics. It provides a class similar to TCanvas.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vintagedave/fully-justified-text\">Fully-justified-text</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vintagedave/fully-justified-text\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">25</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":25,\"repo\":\"vintagedave/fully-justified-text\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> Delphi VCL / Windows project for text output, allowing printing of fully justified text with a variety of options.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Memnarch/AsciiImage\">AsciiImage</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Memnarch/AsciiImage\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">31</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":31,\"repo\":\"Memnarch/AsciiImage\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> AsciiImage-Implementation for Delphi by Alexander Benikowski based on AsciiImage by Charles Parnot. Read more on <a href=\"http://cocoamine.net/blog/2015/03/20/replacing-photoshop-with-nsstring\">his article</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T14:16:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ayr-ton/awesome-geek-podcasts","categoryHTML":"<h2>In English</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hackaday.com/category/podcasts/\">Hackaday Podcast</a> - Hackaday's podcast, talking about the best articles published and hackaday contests.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T12:59:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ayr-ton/awesome-geek-podcasts","categoryHTML":"<h2>In English</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ourludicrousfuture.com/\">Our Ludicrous Future</a> - Mostly talks abut space, technology and Elon Musk.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T12:59:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ayr-ton/awesome-geek-podcasts","categoryHTML":"<h2>In Portuguese</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.portalcafebrasil.com.br/todos/lidercast/\">Lídercast Café Brasil</a> - Entrevistas tratando de assuntos como liderança e empreendedorismo.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T12:59:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ayr-ton/awesome-geek-podcasts","categoryHTML":"<h2>In Portuguese</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://tecnoblog.net/categoria/podcast/\">Tecnocast</a> - Podcast do Tecnoblog, sobre tecnologia.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T12:59:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ayr-ton/awesome-geek-podcasts","categoryHTML":"<h2>In Portuguese</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://xadrezverbal.com/category/audio/podcast-do-xadrez-verbal/\">Xadrez Verbal</a> - Política, história e atualidades.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T12:59:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"shime/creative-commons-media","categoryHTML":"<h2>Video</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://mixkit.co/\">Mixkit</a> - A gallery of high-quality videos and animation</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-08T12:05:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"PatrickJS/awesome-angular","categoryHTML":"<h5><a href=\"